This paper primarily focuses on cybercrime and its impact on individuals, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cybercrime (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the human factors and psychological aspects that cybercriminals exploit, which could be categorized under social and information sciences (cs.SI), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and systems and control (cs.SD).
